SmartWatch Pro X500 User Guide

Getting Started
To power on your SmartWatch Pro X500, press and hold the side button for 3 seconds until the logo appears. The initial setup requires connecting to your smartphone via the SmartWatch app available on iOS and Android.

Battery and Charging
The X500 features a 450mAh battery providing up to 7 days of typical use. Use the magnetic charging dock included in the box. A full charge takes approximately 2 hours. Enable Power Saver mode to extend battery life to 14 days.

Health Monitoring Features
Heart Rate: Continuous monitoring with alerts for unusual patterns above 120 BPM or below 50 BPM at rest.
Sleep Tracking: Automatic detection of sleep stages including light, deep, and REM sleep.
Blood Oxygen: SpO2 measurements available on-demand, with accuracy of Â±2%.
Step Counter: Tracks daily steps with a default goal of 10,000 steps.

Water Resistance
The X500 is water resistant up to 50 meters (5 ATM). Suitable for swimming in pools but not recommended for scuba diving or high-velocity water activities like jet skiing.

Troubleshooting
If the watch becomes unresponsive, perform a force restart by holding both the side button and crown for 10 seconds. For sync issues, ensure Bluetooth is enabled and the watch is within 10 meters of your phone.